DAO = Data Access Object

The job of DAO is ONLY database communication.

DAO should not contain business logic.

Think of it like this:

Controller / Main
        ↓
Service Layer (business logic, transactions)
        ↓
DAO (database operations only)
        ↓
Database

Example responsibilities:

DAO should do

✔ Insert
✔ Update
✔ Delete
✔ Select

Why separate DAO and Service layer?
DAO isolates database logic while Service handles business logic and transactions.
This improves maintainability, testing, and separation of concerns.


